To update your Auto Scaling group with a new launch template, you typically perform the following actions:

You create a new launch template for your Auto Scaling group. For more information, see Create a launch template for an Auto Scaling group.

You configure the minimum healthy percentage, optional checkpoints, and any other settings as needed, specify a desired configuration that includes your launch template, and start an instance refresh. Optionally, your desired configuration can specify whether to apply a mixed instances policy.
